  "text": "Importantly, all tree-ring records shown in AR4 were detrended using a method known as 'Regional Curve Standardization' (RCS; [CITATION_1] . This technique allows the preservation of centennial scale climate variability, even if the tree-ring chronologies are composed of relatively short segments of material from living trees and historical wood [CITATION_2] . Application of RCS is essential to reconstruct the low frequency spectrum of temperature variability including long-term cooling trends ) and thus necessary to estimate the spatial extent of MWP [CITATION_3] .",
